					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This seems to be an <hi rend="italic">uḷvari</hi> document of the <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi</hi> and <hi rend="italic">iṟaiyili</hi> lands comprising the one granted by Ediriliśōḻaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śōḻiyavaraiyar at Dāṉaviṉōdanallūr (in the 25th year of the king?) and another granted in the 16th year of <hi rend="italic">Suṅgantavirtta</hi> Kulōttuṅga-Chōḷa (I) by the <hi rend="italic">Ūravar</hi> (assembly) of Māṅgu[ḍi]? The extent of the lands and their yield in paddy are also given. The inscription being damaged the details are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
